{
  "texts": [
    "S31 of Supplementary Information), we decided to proceed with ParPgb W59L Y60Q (ParLQ) as a starting point (parent) for ALDE.",
    "Because our goal was to arrive at a variant with high yield and high selectivity for the cisproduct, we defined the objective to be explicitly optimized as the difference between the yield of cis-2a and the yield of trans-2a.",
    "The ParLQ variant demonstrates only moderate cyclopropanation yield (~40% yield) and stereoselectivity (3:1 preferring trans-2a) under screening conditions, and no known protein variant of ParPgb has high fitness for our objective.",
    "Based on previous engineering studies using protoglobin scaffolds, we selected five active-site residues (W56, Y57, L59, Q60, and F89; WYLQF) positioned above the distal face of the heme cofactor, which display epistatic effects and are known to impact non-native activity (Fig. 2B) 38, 39.",
    "Single-site saturation mutagenesis (SSM) was performed at these sites, and variants were screened by gas chromatography for their cyclopropanation products."
  ]
}